            <q>The court, on the application of the Regulator, may make such order as the court thinks just and convenient",</q>
            and so on, for ensuring that the proceeds are transferred towards a pension scheme or an annuity or to the liberated member. Unfortunately, I wonder whether the phrase,
            <q>on the application of the Regulator",</q>
            limits the court's powers if the regulator does not apply, but the individual does.
          </p>
        </blockquote>
